NZI Capital Corp, a unit of &lt;NZICorp>, is offering 150 mln dlrs of guaranteed notes due 1997yielding 8.36 pct, said sole manager Kidder, Peabody and CoInc.    The notes have an 8-1/4 pct coupon and were priced at99.261 to yield 115 basis points more than comparable Treasurysecurities. Non-callable for seven years, the issue is ratedA-2 by Moody's Investors Service Inc and A-plus by Standard andPoor's Corp.    The notes will be listed on the New York Stock Exchange.NZI is an insurance company in New Zealand. Reuter&#3;